        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 14 at 5:44PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 544 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms extending from near Keota to near Adena School, or
extending from 36 miles northwest of Fort Morgan to 7 miles south of
Fort Morgan, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Morgan, Brush, Log Lane Village, Hillrose, New Raymer,
Stoneham, Antelope Springs, Snyder, Keota, Pawnee Buttes, Adena
School, Buckingham, Fort Morgan Airport and Union.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Prepare for sudden gusty winds. Secure loose objects and move to a
safe shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
